<body lang=EN-GB style='tab-interval:36.0pt'>

<div class=Section1>

<p class=MsoNormal style='mso-pagination:none'><span style='layout-grid-mode:
line'>Tagelied seems to have embraced Barbarian tavern culture very swiftly,
after a rather shaky start with Jallt in McQuaids dark stout.<span
style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>This was of some concern to the Guild at the
time, but I am of the opinion that such excesses are very common at this stage
of a Bards career, or indeed any career, and in fact in Tagelied’s case were
positively therapeutic, given his rather sheltered upbringing so far…<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='mso-pagination:none'><span style='layout-grid-mode:
line'><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='mso-pagination:none'><span style='layout-grid-mode:
line'>Master Lutestringer, 37th Circle, Historical section, from his
introduction to the compiled travels of Tagelied HalfElven.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='mso-pagination:none'><span style='layout-grid-mode:
line'><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='mso-pagination:none'><span style='layout-grid-mode:
line'><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='mso-pagination:none'><b><u><span style='font-size:
12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:10.0pt;layout-grid-mode:line'>The Fourth Report</span></u></b><b><span
style='font-size:12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:10.0pt;layout-grid-mode:line'>.<o:p></o:p></span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='mso-pagination:none'><span style='layout-grid-mode:
line'><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='mso-pagination:none'><span style='layout-grid-mode:
line'>Your Graces,<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='mso-pagination:none'><span style='layout-grid-mode:
line'><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='mso-pagination:none'><span style='layout-grid-mode:
line'>I must tender my most humble apologies for my delay in preparing this
latest report.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>The next stage of my
investigations has taken far longer than expected to compile.<span
style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>It is only after these past two weeks that I
feel able to detail my findings into the murky world of Barbarian drinking
songs.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-indent:36.0pt;mso-pagination:none'><span
style='layout-grid-mode:line'>Our representative here, Marton Stringsinger, has
been most supportive of my efforts in this work, and I feel I must commend him
to Your Graces.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>I am ashamed to admit
that my initial impressions of the bard were rather negative, as he struck me
as being of a distinctly dilatory disposition.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes"> 
</span>Important mail was treated in a most cavalier manner, and he was rarely
to be seen out of his bed before midday.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes"> 
</span>However, when I asked for his advice as to the direction of my
researches, he displayed a most excellent knowledge of the local culture,
suggesting that extensive field study of Halas taverns would stand the best
chance of yielding examples of Barbarian musical traditions.<span
style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>Nor was this all, for he immediately placed
his entire extensive workload on hold and insisted on accompanying me, citing
the benefits of sharing the local knowledge he had carefully gleaned over the
course of his assignment here.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>Nor was
this all, for he graciously refused to take any credit for his assistance,
asking for his contribution not to be named in this report to Your Graces.<span
style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>After careful consideration however, I have
decided to put aside his suggestion, as I feel his assistance was of such
immense value.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-indent:36.0pt;mso-pagination:none'><span
style='layout-grid-mode:line'><span style="mso-spacerun:
yes"> </span>Accordingly, under his direction, over the next twelve days I
visited each Halas tavern in a cyclical manner.<span style="mso-spacerun:
yes">  </span>Marton was quite clear that this was necessary if examples of Barbarian
singing were not to be overlooked.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>It
did make for long hours, often taking up full three-quarters of the day, and on
several occasions the entire day.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes"> 
</span>Barbarian taverns are noisy, draughty, very uncomfortable places, which
are often also very dangerous.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes"> 
</span>Fortunately Marton was only too glad to handle the accounts with the
local owners, leaving me free to concentrate on recording songs.<span
style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>At first I was greeted with much suspicion,
but as the project proceeded I am proud to say I found myself in some demand,
and many were the acquaintances I made.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes"> 
</span>All in all this was a most trying assignment.<span style="mso-spacerun:
yes">  </span>I also suspect that it may have been a medically inadvisable one.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-indent:36.0pt;mso-pagination:none'><span
style='layout-grid-mode:line'>In the first place these performances are not
exactly undertaken under ideal conditions.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes"> 
</span>Many “songs” were discovered, but the overwhelming majority have had to
be discarded.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>Most were very short,
little more than ditties.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>Many were
unrecognisable, owing to the strong accents of the singers and the general
levels of intoxication they were enduring.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes"> 
</span>A few promising examples have unfortunately been lost.<span
style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>I had to be constantly alive to the
possibility of violence, and had to leave several scripts behind to slake the
fury of the Northmen whose efforts I was recording.<span style="mso-spacerun:
yes">  </span>Also, I have discovered that parchment is unable to withstand
stomach acid.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-indent:36.0pt;mso-pagination:none'><span
style='layout-grid-mode:line'>Secondly, and more importantly, there are a great
many Barbarian drinking songs.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>In fact
it would be more accurate to say that Barbarian songs that are NOT drinking
songs are in a considerable minority.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>I
even once discovered what I took to be a rather sickly love ballad.<span
style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>It was only until it was nearly finished
that I realised the object of affection of the singer was not some Barbarian
wench but a type of pale ale.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>I have
not recorded it here.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>It is a truly
terrible song.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-indent:36.0pt;mso-pagination:none'><span
style='layout-grid-mode:line'>Suffice it to say that drinking is a national
pastime for the Barbarians of Halas.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>It
is perhaps because there is little else to do here, other than to create and
destroy life.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>On that score, I was
hoping to record a Barbarian courtship ceremony, but this proved a completely
fruitless project.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>Jallt assured me
this combined singing/dancing/fighting event was a most pleasing spectacle,
attracting large audiences.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>However,
when I was finally fortunate enough to be present at one, it seemed to consist
largely of shouting at and hitting the prospective partner with an assortment
of blunt instruments.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>When I pointed
this out to Jallt, who was watching the proceedings with some approval, she
expressed the opinion that perhaps something had been lost in translation.<span
style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>I admit that there are many facets and
nuances of Barbarian culture that still elude me, but I have to say I find it
difficult to imagine how it is possible to misread striking someone on the back
of the head with a mammoth tusk.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-indent:36.0pt;mso-pagination:none'><span
style='layout-grid-mode:line'>The final point I would make is that Barbarians
do not endure the rigors of censorship well and have little idea of the
propriety of good order and moral discipline.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes"> 
</span>Some of the imagery in their poetry is explicit beyond any idea of
obscenity.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>I admit I found most of this
- amusing, but of course, quite unsuitable for any kind of public
performance.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>Definitely.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoBodyTextIndent>So what I have included here is the best of the
Barbarian drinking songs.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>Perhaps more
accurately, I should say I have included the least worst of the Barbarian
drinking songs.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>On this score I have
been forced to discard such works as “Hit them with a very large axe”; “Lady
Vox, has the ***”; and<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>“The mating
habits of Mammoths”.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>I would venture to
suggest that guidelines should be put in place to govern admittance to even
these records once they have been archived, in the spirit of public decency and
good order.</p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-indent:36.0pt;mso-pagination:none'><span
style='layout-grid-mode:line'>In all cases the titles are my own suggestions.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='mso-pagination:none'><span style='layout-grid-mode:
line'><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='mso-pagination:none'><span style='layout-grid-mode:
line'><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='mso-pagination:none'><b><u><span style='font-size:
12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:10.0pt;layout-grid-mode:line'>Skol</span></u></b><b><span
style='font-size:12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:10.0pt;layout-grid-mode:line'>!<o:p></o:p></span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='mso-pagination:none'><span style='layout-grid-mode:
line'><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='mso-pagination:none'><span style='layout-grid-mode:
line'>Accompaniment – Multiple tankards, banging on tabletops.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='mso-pagination:none'><span style='layout-grid-mode:
line'>Pace: Medium.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='mso-pagination:none'><span style='layout-grid-mode:
