Skol!<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>Skol!<span style="mso-spacerun:
yes">  </span>Skol! Skol! ..etc etc, ad infinitum….<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='mso-pagination:none'><span style='layout-grid-mode:
line'><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='mso-pagination:none'><span style='layout-grid-mode:
line'>All social gatherings I witnessed included at least one rendition of this
alleged “classic”.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>It is something that
is frankly beyond any kind of criticism or parody.<span style="mso-spacerun:
yes">  </span>It is possibly the archetypal Barbarian drinking song.<span
style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>The problem is that most of them have
difficulty remembering the words, especially after their twenty-third pint of
extra-strong “brain-seizure beer”, an appalling concoction brewed from Gnoll
pup scalps and tundra weed.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-indent:36.0pt;mso-pagination:none'><span
style='layout-grid-mode:line'>“Skol” is a cultural specific term - basically a
wish for good health, long life, and getting the next round of drinks in.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='mso-pagination:none'><span style='layout-grid-mode:
line'><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='mso-pagination:none'><span style='layout-grid-mode:
line'><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='mso-pagination:none'><b><u><span style='font-size:
12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:10.0pt;layout-grid-mode:line'>The Origins song</span></u></b><b><span
style='font-size:12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:10.0pt;layout-grid-mode:line'>.<o:p></o:p></span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='mso-pagination:none'><span style='layout-grid-mode:
