<p class=MsoNormal style='mso-pagination:none'><span style='layout-grid-mode:
line'><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='mso-pagination:none'><span style='layout-grid-mode:
line'>**** with sword, skewer with axe!<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='mso-pagination:none'><span style='layout-grid-mode:
line'>Damage *** **** *** to the max!<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='mso-pagination:none'><span style='layout-grid-mode:
line'>Tra-la-la-la, la-la-la, la-lah!<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='mso-pagination:none'><span style='layout-grid-mode:
line'><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='mso-pagination:none'><span style='layout-grid-mode:
line'>**** with **, **** up ****!<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='mso-pagination:none'><span style='layout-grid-mode:
line'>** spike *** ** *** sideways!<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='mso-pagination:none'><span style='layout-grid-mode:
line'>***-la-la-la, ****-la-la, la-****<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='mso-pagination:none'><span style='layout-grid-mode:
line'><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='mso-pagination:none'><span style='layout-grid-mode:
line'>The lyrics go rather downhill after this, and it really would be an
affront to you, the honoured members of the Guild, not to mention my vows to
Rodcet Nife, to elaborate further.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>This
song is interesting in that it is one of the very few drinking songs that mix
solo singing with choral (i.e. everyone joins in for the rudimentary chorus
that is every third line).<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>I can
testify that in spite of its crudity, this is a very effective tool for
audience participation.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='mso-pagination:none'><span style='layout-grid-mode:
line'><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='mso-pagination:none'><span style='layout-grid-mode:
line'><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoPlainText><b><u><span style='font-size:12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:
10.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman";mso-fareast-font-family:"MS Mincho"'>The
Everfrost lament</span></u></b><b><span style='font-size:12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:
10.0pt;font-family:"Times New Roman";mso-fareast-font-family:"MS Mincho"'>.<o:p></o:p></span></b></p>

<p class=MsoPlainText><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman";mso-fareast-font-family:
"MS Mincho"'><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='mso-pagination:none'><span style='layout-grid-mode:
line'>Accompaniment – Acappella.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoPlainText><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman";layout-grid-mode:
line'>Pace: Slowly, with feeling.</span><span style='layout-grid-mode:line'><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoPlainText><span style='layout-grid-mode:line'><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoPlainText><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman";mso-fareast-font-family:
"MS Mincho"'>Come all you valiant Warriors, a tale I will tell,<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoPlainText><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman";mso-fareast-font-family:
"MS Mincho"'>About the bloody battle, that was fought on Everfrost Hill.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoPlainText><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman";mso-fareast-font-family:
"MS Mincho"'>It was an awful struggle, that terrible week of June,<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoPlainText><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman";mso-fareast-font-family:
"MS Mincho"'>A mighty fearful struggle, fought beneath the moon.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoPlainText><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman";mso-fareast-font-family:
"MS Mincho"'><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoPlainText><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman";mso-fareast-font-family:
"MS Mincho"'>It was the twenty-second, just at the end of day,<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoPlainText><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman";mso-fareast-font-family:
"MS Mincho"'>Our army was assembling, about to move away.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoPlainText><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman";mso-fareast-font-family:
"MS Mincho"'>My feelings at that moment, I do remember well,<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoPlainText><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman";mso-fareast-font-family:
"MS Mincho"'>Little did I realise, on what I would have to dwell.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoPlainText><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman";mso-fareast-font-family:
"MS Mincho"'><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoPlainText><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman";mso-fareast-font-family:
"MS Mincho"'>About that very hour, the alarm went loud and clear,<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoPlainText><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman";mso-fareast-font-family:
"MS Mincho"'>We rushed to arms all eager, for no foe did we fear.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoPlainText><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman";mso-fareast-font-family:
"MS Mincho"'>The horrors of that battle, still fill my soul with dread,<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoPlainText><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman";mso-fareast-font-family:
"MS Mincho"'>I hear the wounded crying, and the silence of the dead.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoPlainText><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman";mso-fareast-font-family:
"MS Mincho"'><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoPlainText><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman";mso-fareast-font-family:
"MS Mincho"'>All the North was gathered, all of us were there,<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoPlainText><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman";mso-fareast-font-family:
"MS Mincho"'>Before the struggle ended, all had said a prayer.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoPlainText><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman";mso-fareast-font-family:
"MS Mincho"'>There was folk from every clanhold, numbered with the slain,<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoPlainText><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman";mso-fareast-font-family:
"MS Mincho"'>There was folk from every family, whose hearts were filled with
pain.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoPlainText><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman";mso-fareast-font-family:
"MS Mincho"'><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoPlainText><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman";mso-fareast-font-family:
"MS Mincho"'>And so it was for half a day, we stood upon our arms,<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoPlainText><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman";mso-fareast-font-family:
"MS Mincho"'>So heavy was the slaughter, a death caused no alarms.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoPlainText><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman";mso-fareast-font-family:
"MS Mincho"'>With death all around us, with suffering by our side,<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoPlainText><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman";mso-fareast-font-family:
"MS Mincho"'>We grew so cold and heartless, to our friends who had died.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoPlainText><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman";mso-fareast-font-family:
"MS Mincho"'><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoPlainText><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman";mso-fareast-font-family:
"MS Mincho"'>And now my song has ended, about that bloody day,<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoPlainText><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman";mso-fareast-font-family:
"MS Mincho"'>I hope the sight shall ne'er be touched again, by the suns rays.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoPlainText><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman";mso-fareast-font-family:
"MS Mincho"'>When unmindful of the wounded, unmindful of the dead,<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoPlainText><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman";mso-fareast-font-family:
"MS Mincho"'>From hour to hour we fought until the river ran red,<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoPlainText><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman";mso-fareast-font-family:
"MS Mincho"'><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoPlainText><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman";mso-fareast-font-family:
"MS Mincho"'>No one knows who wrote this song, but it is certainly very, very
old.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>It seems to describe one of the
many fierce battles fought against the Orcs to consolidate Barbarian presence
in the Halas area.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>It tends to be sung
late in the evening, when the assembled company have entered the “maudlin
stage”.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoPlainText><span style='font-family:"Times New Roman";mso-fareast-font-family:
"MS Mincho"'><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='mso-pagination:none'><span style='layout-grid-mode:
line'><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='mso-pagination:none'><b><u><span style='font-size:
12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:10.0pt;layout-grid-mode:line'>Conclusions</span></u></b><b><span
style='font-size:12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:10.0pt;layout-grid-mode:line'>.<o:p></o:p></span></b></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='mso-pagination:none'><span style='layout-grid-mode:
line'><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='mso-pagination:none'><span style='layout-grid-mode:
line'>What, therefore, are we to make of all this?<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-indent:36.0pt;mso-pagination:none'><span
style='layout-grid-mode:line'>In addition to their close alliance to the
brewing industry, Barbarian songs have another common feature.<span
style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>They tend to be very affirmative, extolling
the virtues of the Barbarian folk, their customs, traditions, past triumphs and
so on.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>This, of course, is not an
uncommon trait.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>Most cultures in
Norrath use music to bolster their sense of identity and self-esteem.<span
style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>However, the Barbarians, as with so many
things in life, tend to extremes in this regard.<span style="mso-spacerun:
yes">  </span>I have no doubt that the absence of considered social structures
as found in, for example Human culture, is partly compensated for by Barbarian
music.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoBodyTextIndent>Once again I have been impressed by the method
rather than the technique.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>From a
purely technical viewpoint these songs are quite appallingly.<span
style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>The rhyme is shallow, the meter is
disjointed, the performances bad beyond belief.<span style="mso-spacerun:
yes">  </span>However, they make up for these deficiencies by sheer energy.<span
style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>Barbarian culture does exist, and it
possesses an exuberance; a vitality; a sheer zest for life and living that
perhaps we, the civilised, have left behind us.<span style="mso-spacerun:
yes">  </span>Perhaps, when life is spontaneous, and but for the moment, it has
more meaning than when planned out in schedules and calendars.<span
style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>This is supposition on my part, but I tell
you truth, I have never seen such audience reaction as I have seen here.<span
style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>Barbarians are tough, and yet I have seen
them reduced to tears of sorrow by a performance of the “Everfrost lament”.</p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='text-indent:36.0pt;mso-pagination:none'><span
style='layout-grid-mode:line'>Your Graces, I have also to report a serious
deficit in my expenses.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>I would ask
your Graces to bear in mind that prices here in Halas are much higher than in
Qeynos, owing to the long distances that supplies must travel and the general
scarcity of merchants willing to undertake the journey, which is both dangerous
and yielding of little profit.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>Also, it
was necessary to entertain the locals in order to gain their trust and
friendship.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>This was also very
expensive, as Barbarians are highly clannish and suspicious of outsiders.<span
style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>They also possess a quite awesome capacity
for alcoholic beverages.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>As such, I
would be most grateful if Your Graces would be able to extend more credit to
this worthy project, that you yourselves were wise enough to commission.<span
style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>The need is rather urgent, and I trust the
renowned generosity of the League will be sufficient to prevent one of their
loyal servants from falling into destitution.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='mso-pagination:none'><span style='layout-grid-mode:
line'><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='mso-pagination:none'><span style='layout-grid-mode:
line'>Written this day by my hand,<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='mso-pagination:none'><span style='layout-grid-mode:
line'><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='mso-pagination:none'><span style='layout-grid-mode:
line'>Tagelied HalfElven, of the 6th Circle, Antonican league of Bards.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='mso-pagination:none'><span style='layout-grid-mode:
line'><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='mso-pagination:none'><span style='layout-grid-mode:
line'><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='mso-pagination:none'><span style='layout-grid-mode:
line'>[ BY ORDER OF THE HIGH COUNCIL OF THE ANTONICAN LEAGUE OF BARDS, MARTON
STRINGSINGER TO BE CONSIDERED FOR SUITABLILITY TO CABILIS POSTING.<span
style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>GIVEN THIS DAY BY MY HAND, EVE MARSINGER]<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='mso-pagination:none'><span style='layout-grid-mode:
line'><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='mso-pagination:none'><span style='layout-grid-mode:
line'><span style="mso-spacerun: yes"> </span><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='mso-pagination:none'><span style='layout-grid-mode:
line'>(You can find both Tagelied and Jallt on the Tholuxe Paells server).<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal style='mso-pagination:none'><span style='layout-grid-mode:
line'><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal><![if !supportEmptyParas]>&nbsp;<![endif]><o:p></o:p></p>

</div>

</body>

